In July 2020, six-year-old Bridger Walker from Cheyenne, Wyoming, became a global hero after bravely protecting his younger sister from a dog attack. Despite his injuries, he managed to lead his sister to safety. Bridger later told his family, âIf someone had to die, I thought it should be me.â ï¿¼

A year after the incident, Bridgerâs father reported that his sonâs recovery was progressing well, with significant improvement in his scars. Bridger expressed pride in his scar, viewing it as a symbol of protecting his sister. ï¿¼
